{"word":"ἁμαρτία","slug":"ἁμαρτία","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἁμαρτία</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἁμαρτάνω'><el>ἁμαρτάνω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>a failure, fault, sin</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>ἁμ. τινός</el> <i>a fault committed by</i> one, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; <el>ἁμ. δόξης</el> <i>fault</i> of judgment, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>generally, <i>guilt, sin</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristotle'>Arist.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}